HEADWORD: Sublieutenant
<hw>Sub`lieu*ten"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub</ets> + <ets>lieutenant</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>sous-lieutenant</ets>.]</ety> <def>An inferior or second
lieutenant; in the British service, a commissioned officer of the lowest
rank.</def>⟦br⟧
